# Proxy mode (default): used by most demos
# The proxy server holds the API key and forwards requests to Runtype.
VITE_PROXY_PORT=43111
# VITE_PROXY_URL=http://localhost:43111

# Client token mode: used by client-token-demo and action-middleware-demo.
# This token should be bound to the action-middleware "Persona Example Agent"
# (its system prompt mandates the {"action":...} envelope that action-middleware
# parses). Do NOT point plain-chat demos at it — see VITE_CLIENT_TOKEN_SIMPLE_CHAT below.
# Create a client token via the Runtype dashboard or POST /v1/client-tokens.
# Client tokens are browser-safe (origin-locked, rate-limited, session-scoped).
# Page context is sent as /v1/client/chat `inputs` (root template vars: {{page_url}}, {{page_elements}}, …).
# Update your Runtype agent system prompt from {{_record.metadata.page_*}} to {{page_*}} when using inputs-only.
# VITE_CLIENT_TOKEN=ct_live_...

# Simple-chat client token: used by feedback-integration-demo.
# Bind this to a *conversational* agent (no action protocol, no tools). The
# feedback demo only exercises message feedback, so reusing VITE_CLIENT_TOKEN's
# action-middleware agent would render raw {"action":"message"} JSON as text.
# Falls back to VITE_CLIENT_TOKEN when unset.
# VITE_CLIENT_TOKEN_SIMPLE_CHAT=ct_live_...

# Override the Runtype API base URL (client token mode only).
# Defaults to https://api.runtype.com when not set.
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8787

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# WebMCP demo (webmcp-demo.html): proxy mode, like the other demos
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The WebMCP demo runs entirely through the local proxy (VITE_PROXY_PORT above).
# Its agent is defined in code as WEBMCP_STOREFRONT_FLOW and mounted at
# /api/chat/dispatch-webmcp: no client token or hosted Runtype agent required.
# To back it with your own Runtype flow instead, set FLOW_ID_WEBMCP on the proxy
# (examples/vercel-edge/src/server.ts).

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# WebMCP Calendar Copilot (webmcp-calendar.html): proxy mode, like the others
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# A calendar dashboard where the docked Persona copilot and Chrome DevTools MCP
# call the same ten WebMCP tools. Adapted from
# https://github.com/WebMCP-org/chrome-devtools-quickstart (MIT).
# Runs entirely through the local proxy (VITE_PROXY_PORT above). Its agent is
# defined in code as WEBMCP_CALENDAR_FLOW and mounted at
# /api/chat/dispatch-calendar: no client token or hosted Runtype agent
# required. To back it with your own Runtype flow instead, set
# FLOW_ID_CALENDAR on the proxy (examples/vercel-edge/src/server.ts).
# Append ?mode=pill for the composer-bar pill variant of the docked panel.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Theme Copilot sidebar (theme.html): proxy mode, like the other demos
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The Theme Editor's docked Theme Copilot runs entirely through the local proxy
# (VITE_PROXY_PORT above). Its agent is defined in code as THEME_ASSISTANT_FLOW
# and mounted at /api/chat/dispatch-theme: no client token or hosted Runtype
# agent required. To back it with your own Runtype flow instead, set
# FLOW_ID_THEME_ASSISTANT on the proxy (examples/vercel-edge/src/server.ts);
# the flow's model must emit native tool calls and accept image input (the
# copilot's reference-image loop sends images both in user messages and in
# screenshot_preview tool results).
